conditions.desc: PATIENT AND/OR SPOUSE'S EGHP IS SECONDARY TO MEDICARE
conditions.instructionDesc: This code indicates that, in response to MSP development questions, the patient and/or their spouse indicates that one or both are employed and there is group health insurance from an EGHP or other employer-sponsored or provided health insurance.  However, either the EGHP is a single employer plan and the employer has fewer than 20 full- and part-time employees, or the EGHP is a multi- or multiple-employer plan that elects to pay secondary to Medicare for employees and spouses aged 65 and older for the participating employers who have fewer than 20 employees.
This code indicates that the patient needed a private room for medical reasons.

This code indicates that the bill is for special dialysis services that involved teaching the patient and helper (if necessary) to perform dialysis.
